Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British beef mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the
mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's
> no pink in the middle.

Put the @couscous{120%g} into a #bowl{}.

Pour in the @boiling water{240%ml} and stir in half the @chicken stock paste{20%g}.

Cover tightly with #cling film{}. Leave to the side, ~{10%minutes}.

Drain the fat from the mince. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic to the beef and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Stir in the
@tomato passata{1%carton}, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer
things milder), @honey{1%tbsp}, @butter{20%g} and the remaining chicken stock
paste.

Bring to the boil and simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Fluff the couscous up with a #fork{}. Share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the chipotle beef.

Add a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}.

Enjoy!